    "body": "Problem: When Neovim is built with Zig, `:checkhealth` falsely reports\n\"Non-optimized debug build\" for release builds. The extraction regex\nstops at the first space, and the validation regex only lists CMake\nbuild type names.\n\nSolution: Fix the extraction regex to capture the full build type string\nand add Zig optimization levels (ReleaseFast, ReleaseSafe, ReleaseSmall)\nto the validation regex.\n\nAI-assisted: Claude Code\n\n<!--\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\n  If this is your first time, check out\n  https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\n  for our PR guidelines.\n-->\n\n## Problem\n\n## Solution\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-08T08:33:26Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "A few notes that were not in the topline:\r\n\r\n- This a first contrib, so apologies for any glaring errors in the\r\n  submission style.\r\n\r\n- The aim is to fix status reports in `checkhealth vim.health` when\r\n  building with Zig. Previously I could build release builds but receive\r\n  warnings because about the build being a debug build (see artifacts\r\n  below for exmaple).\r\n\r\n- This is basically a one-liner to account for different names in Zig\r\n  build artifacts so that `checkhealth vim.health` produces accurate\r\n  warnings.\r\n\r\n- Testing in `tests/functional/plugin/health_spec.lua` and the\r\n  surrounding fixtures appear only to stub expected layouts for the\r\n  `checkhealth` menu. Adding tests for built artifacts clearly went\r\n  against the style of what is in the suite currently, and seemed like\r\n  it could not be anchored to anything concretely discernible about the\r\n  build system. Therefore I have not modified the test suite at all.\r\n\r\n- In lui of tests, I did build every Zig build (make builds crash on my\r\n  machine) to verify behavior in built editors. Below are the relevant\r\n  snippets from those artifacts.\r\n\r\n```checkhealth\r\n[zig build Doptimize=Debug]\r\n==============================================================================\r\nvim.health:                                                               2 ⚠️\r\n\r\nPerformance ~\r\n- Build type: zig build -Doptimize=Debug\r\n- ⚠️ WARNING Non-optimized debug build. Nvim will be slower.\r\n  - ADVICE:\r\n    - Install a different Nvim package, or rebuild with `CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo` (CMake) or `-Doptimize=ReleaseFast` (Zig).\r\n    - https://neovim.io/doc/build/#building\r\n```\r\n\r\nNOTE: Previously, building with `zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseFast` (or\r\nany other release build) would have emitted the same warning as above.\r\nThe new reports from `checkhealth vim.health` are as follows:\r\n\r\n```checkhealth\r\n[zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseFast]\r\n==============================================================================\r\nvim.health:                                                               1 ⚠️\r\n\r\nPerformance ~\r\n- ✅ OK Build type: zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseFast\r\n\r\n\r\n[zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSafe]\r\n==============================================================================\r\nvim.health:                                                               1 ⚠️\r\n\r\nPerformance ~\r\n- ✅ OK Build type: zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSafe\r\n\r\nRemote Plugins ~\r\n- ✅ OK Up to date\r\n\r\n\r\n[zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSmall]\r\n==============================================================================\r\nvim.health:                                                               1 ⚠️\r\n\r\nPerformance ~\r\n- ✅ OK Build type: zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSmall\r\n```\r\n",
            "created_at": "2026-04-05T23:08:39Z",
